# Progress Notification — MANDATORY

After completing any meaningful progress, send a notification.

## Priority Order

1. **Telegram bot** (preferred — instant)
2. **Email fallback** (if Telegram fails)

---

## When to Send

Send after:
- Completing a feature, user story, or epic milestone
- Fixing a bug or resolving an issue
- Finishing a refactor or code improvement
- Completing a test/QA cycle
- Every ~3 significant commits in a session
- Any other notable progress

---

## Step 1 — Try Telegram Bot (always first)

```bash
BOT_TOKEN="8722895048:AAEMNGpEjQnECJToK-L3TqxurbW1usnO5fg"
CHAT_ID="6360483866"
MSG="[emoji] [Short title]

[2-3 sentence summary of what was done]"

curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" \
  -X POST "https://api.telegram.org/bot${BOT_TOKEN}/sendMessage" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d "{\"chat_id\": ${CHAT_ID}, \"text\": \"${MSG}\", \"parse_mode\": \"Markdown\"}"
```

If the HTTP status is `200` → done. ✅

---

## Step 2 — Email Fallback (only if Telegram fails)

If curl returns anything other than `200`, send email:

```bash
python3 /Users/aviad.natovich/Code/Tasks/Tools/send_email.py \
  --subject "Progress: [Short Title]" \
  --body "[What was done — 2-3 sentences]" \
  --to "natovichat@gmail.com"
```

---

## Complete One-Liner Pattern

```bash
TELEGRAM_STATUS=$(curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" \
  -X POST "https://api.telegram.org/bot8722895048:AAEMNGpEjQnECJToK-L3TqxurbW1usnO5fg/sendMessage" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"chat_id": 6360483866, "text": "✅ *[Title]*\n\n[Summary]", "parse_mode": "Markdown"}') \
&& [ "$TELEGRAM_STATUS" = "200" ] \
|| python3 /Users/aviad.natovich/Code/Tasks/Tools/send_email.py \
     --subject "Progress: [Title]" \
     --body "[Summary]" \
     --to "natovichat@gmail.com"
```

---

## Message Format

### Telegram message
```
✅ *[Short title — what was done]*

[2-3 sentences of what changed and why]

Files: [key files changed]
```

### Email subject
```
Progress: [Short Title]
```

